  "text": "# ABOUT RATES & INTEREST  \n**Q: Why do interest rates change?**\nA: Bank of England (BoE) changes its base rate based on economic conditions. We pass these changes to customers (our 2.5% margin stays fixed).  \n**Q: When does FirstUK change rates?**\nA: Monthly (typically mid-month). We notify customers via email before changes take effect.  \n**Q: Can I lock in a rate?**\nA: SmartSaver is variable. For fixed rates, consider fixed-rate bonds (coming 2026).  \n**Q: How is interest calculated?**\nA: Daily calculation, paid monthly. Example: £10,000 at 4.50% AER earns ~£37.50 per month.  \n---",
